{
  "page": "Jon Mertyns",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"infobox\" style=\"min-width:22em;max-width:32em;border-collapse:separate;border-spacing:3px\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;font-weight:bold; background: none; line-height: 1.1em;\"><table style=\"width:100%\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:top;text-align:left;width:50px\"><a href=\"/index.php/House_Mertyns\" title=\"House Mertyns\"><img alt=\"House Mertyns.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/e/e2/House_Mertyns.svg/50px-House_Mertyns.svg.png\" width=\"50\" height=\"55\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/e/e2/House_Mertyns.svg/75px-House_Mertyns.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/e/e2/House_Mertyns.svg/100px-House_Mertyns.svg.png 2x\" /></a></td><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:middle;text-align:center;padding:0px 7px 5px 7px\"><span style=\"font-size:80%;font-weight:normal\"> Lord</span><br />Jon Mertyns</td><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:top;text-align:right;width:50px\"><a href=\"/index.php/House_Mertyns\" title=\"House Mertyns\"><img alt=\"House Mertyns.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/e/e2/House_Mertyns.svg/50px-House_Mertyns.svg.png\" width=\"50\" height=\"55\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/e/e2/House_Mertyns.svg/75px-House_Mertyns.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/e/e2/House_Mertyns.svg/100px-House_Mertyns.svg.png 2x\" /></a></td></tr></tbody></table></th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\"></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Title</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Lord_of_Mistwood\" title=\"Lord of Mistwood\">Lord of Mistwood</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Allegiance</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/House_Mertyns\" title=\"House Mertyns\">House Mertyns</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Culture</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Stormlander\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Stormlander\">Stormlander</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Book</th><td>\n<i><a href=\"/index.php/Fire_%26_Blood\" title=\"Fire &amp; Blood\">Fire &amp; Blood</a></i> (mentioned)</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><b>Jon Mertyns</b> was the Lord of <a href=\"/index.php/Mistwood\" title=\"Mistwood\">Mistwood</a> and head of <a href=\"/index.php/House_Mertyns\" title=\"House Mertyns\">House Mertyns</a> during the early reign of King <a href=\"/index.php/Jaehaerys_I_Targaryen\" title=\"Jaehaerys I Targaryen\">Jaehaerys I Targaryen</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_year_of_the_three_brides_-_49_ac.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_year_of_the_three_brides_-_49_ac.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Jon_Mertyns&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Lord Jon attended the <a href=\"/index.php/Golden_Wedding\" title=\"Golden Wedding\">Golden Wedding</a>, where the king entertained the <a href=\"/index.php/Lord\" title=\"Lord\">lords</a> in the intimacy of his <a href=\"/index.php/Solar\" title=\"Solar\">solar</a>, encouraging them to speak freely and share their views on the problems of the <a href=\"/index.php/Seven_Kingdoms\" title=\"Seven Kingdoms\">realm</a> and how they might best be overcome. Lord Jon approved of Jaehaerys, saying, \"He laughs often and freely, even at himself.\"<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_year_of_the_three_brides_-_49_ac.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_year_of_the_three_brides_-_49_ac.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Jon_Mertyns&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rfabthe_year_of_the_three_brides_-_49_ac.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabthe_year_of_the_three_brides_-_49_ac.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">1.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabthe_year_of_the_three_brides_-_49_ac.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\">1.1</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/Fire_%26_Blood\" title=\"Fire &amp; Blood\">Fire &amp; Blood</a></i>, The Year of the Three Brides - 49 AC.</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20260403092634\nCache expiry: 1209600\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.066 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.247 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 526/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 10430/1000000\nPost‐expand include size: 5280/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 596/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 7/40\nExpensive parser function count: 0/100\nUnstrip recursion depth: 0/20\nUnstrip post‐expand size: 1045/5000000 bytes\nLua time usage: 0.160/7.000 seconds\nLua virtual size: 6.45 MB/50 MB\nLua estimated memory usage: 0 bytes\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%  238.137      1 -total\n 96.80%  230.515      1 Template:Infobox_character\n 95.96%  228.508      1 Template:Infobox\n 11.13%   26.513     12 Template:Infobox_value\n  4.79%   11.408      4 Template:Infobox_label\n  2.48%    5.911      2 Template:Ref\n  1.69%    4.019      2 Template:Ref/core\n  0.63%    1.507      1 Template:References\n  0.41%    0.965      1 Template:Main_other\n-->\n</div>\n<!-- Saved in parser cache w